bug.short_desc: Parts dependency problem with DateFormat class

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1136 Application configuration file
The following is a quote from the forum topic titled "Parts question" started on March 12, 2012.
"Instantiating the DateFormat class to initialize a map member lifts all runtime dependencies of the constructor to loadtime dependencies of webrf.Statics. This should have been detected, and the MBindings mixin and the SingleValueBinding class should have been sorted appropriately."
Created attachment 1138 Output from running generate.py source
Created attachment 1139 Output from running generate.py source -v

My typo mistake, I actually had:
DATEFORMAT_MDY: new qx.util.format.DateFormat("MM/dd/yyyy"),

(In reply to comment #6) > That said, I don't believe it works to initialize a static member with an > instance of a class within the statics section.
I think it's perfectly fine to initialize a static member with a class instance. Just check this older bug#1455 where this was exactly the test case. (In this light, the current bug is a regression).

Workaround:
Ed,
the problem arises with a hard-to-track dependency in the DateFormat constructor. If you still want to use the statics initialization, as a work-around you should be able to fix it by adding the following line to the comment (either existing or you have to create it) near the top of your webrf.Statics class:
/* #require(qx.data.SingleValueBinding) */
The issue is the same for the app with or without using parts, but using parts uncovers it.

If you still want to use the statics initialization, as a > work-around you should be able to fix it by adding the following line to the > comment (either existing or you have to create it) near the top of your > webrf.Statics class: > > /* > #require(qx.data.SingleValueBinding) > */ > > The issue is the same for the app with or without using parts, but using parts > uncovers it.
